## React & Next.js

### Server vs Client Components
- Default to React Server Components (RSC)
- Add `"use client"` only when needed: event handlers, hooks, browser APIs
- Never expose sensitive data from Server Components to Client Components

### App Router Conventions
- Use `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx` per segment
- Use `not-found.tsx` for 404 handling
- Use `next/navigation` (never `next/router`)

### Data Fetching
- Fetch data directly in Server Components
- Avoid unnecessary API Route Handlers; prefer Server Actions
- Server Actions go in `app/actions/[feature].ts` with `"use server"` directive
- Use `use cache` + `revalidateTag` for caching in Next.js 16

### TypeScript
- Strict mode always on, never use `any`
- Prefer `type` over `interface` unless merging is needed
- Use `satisfies` operator where appropriate
- Shared types exported from `lib/types.ts` (or `lib/types/`)

### Error Handling
- Always handle loading and error states in UI
- Async functions must have try/catch or use Result pattern
- Use `error.tsx` boundaries for route-level errors